name: Ruby Droplets under a Crescent Moon Necklace
description: This necklace just kept growing when I was building it.  The flow from wings down to the dangling red stone is really smooth and triangular.  You might say that I've included some pagan symbolism here, which is not denied...but not entirely intentional either.  A great fall/winter piece for the Stevie Nicks in you!

name: Back-Yard Time Travel Pyramid
description:
Do you like to find tiny details hidden in an image?  This is a 3-D version of such a thing.  I've hidden little bits of ephemera found in the yard of my 1930's home in the Southwest.  You will find a tiny bit of robin's egg, a shred of wasp nest, a bit of glass from a very old Dr. Pepper Bottle, a few shiny jewels, a feather from a roseate spoonbill (okay, that's from my job at the zoo) and more.   

If you run out of conversation... well, you won't... not with this around.

name: On Wings of Flowers Necklace
description:
Art Deco has always been one of the most elegant, feminine ways to interpret lines.  Not superfluous or overly sweet, yet soft in all the right places.  

This necklace is lightweight and smooth.  I can see it looking great with velvets, laces and leathers.  But really that's up to you.

name: Hammered Citrine Drop Earrings
description:
Elegant, unusual, and smooth...just like you.  Controversial?  A little. Sparkly?  Very.  

Setting a facetted square citrine on the side makes folks look twice, and say, 'hmmm!'  

1.75" Long by .5" wide.

name: Lucky Charm Necklace
description: It's magically delicious... and almost guaranteed to charm drinks out of your friends.  Well, maybe not.  But it's pretty cute, and you cannot deny that two superstitious charms are better than one.  Four leaf clover versus horse-shoe... what's your fave?  Silvertone with antique buffing.
